<dl id="n34030a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34030a">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34030a"> 30(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> change sign of / lower line &amp; proceed in the / addition</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Subtraction: &hellip; It is, however, more convenient to arrange the work as follows, <mark>the signs of all the terms in the lower line being changed</mark>. &hellip; <br><b>Rule</b>. <mark>Change the sign</mark> of every term in the expression to be subtracted, <mark>and add</mark> to the other expression. <small> Hall &amp; Knight, <a name="HSHK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HSHK"><cite title="source">Elementary Algebra for Schools</cite></a> (n.d) 20</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
